# Payments Risk Data Science Portfolio

This repository showcases my end-to-end learning and practical implementation of **Data Science applied to Payments, Fraud Detection, and AML Transaction Monitoring**.

The focus is on **real-world banking and fintech use cases**, combining domain expertise with Python, SQL, Machine Learning, and explainable AI.

---

## üîç Problem Domains Covered
- Card & Account Fraud Detection
- AML Transaction Monitoring
- Payment Risk Scoring
- Cross-Border Transaction Risk
- Rule-Based + ML Hybrid Systems
- Model Explainability for Regulators

---

## üß† Skills & Tools
- **Programming:** Python, SQL  
- **Libraries:** pandas, numpy, scikit-learn, XGBoost, SHAP  
- **Analytics:** Feature Engineering, Statistical Analysis  
- **ML Models:** Logistic Regression, Tree-based Models, Anomaly Detection  
- **Visualization:** Power BI / Tableau  
- **Payments Domain:** SWIFT, SEPA, ISO 20022, AML/KYC  

---

## üìÅ Repository Structure

### 00_domain_foundations
Core understanding of payments, fraud types, and AML workflows.

### 01_data_analysis_sql_python
Exploratory analysis of transaction data and SQL-based fraud detection logic.

### 02_feature_engineering
Creation of domain-driven features such as velocity, behavioral, and geo-risk indicators.

### 03_models
Implementation and evaluation of supervised and unsupervised ML models for fraud detection.

### 04_aml_risk_scoring
End-to-end AML transaction monitoring system with alert generation.

### 05_model_explainability
Explainable AI techniques to justify model decisions to compliance and regulators.

### 06_dashboarding
Risk and fraud monitoring dashboards for business stakeholders.

